\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid11099359 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5916634\charrsid14709753  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1270686\charrsid14709753 an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
you give me your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well now, that's telling tales out of school, I'll tell you why. Ooh and it's perfectly true because - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Your real name is? Henry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Henry Frank Ross. Now I deserted a British ship round about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname metricconverter}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname ProductID}{\xmlattrvalue 1909 in}}}1909 in{\*\xmlclose} Galveston, Texas and - er - I went - work along the coast there for a bit and - it was in 
1910 - my mother was in a bad position - a bad way - my dad died 1900. I came home but - when I went to the consul to see if there was a ship going home - the British Sun was the name of the oil-tanker I couldn't give me name as Ross.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Because they'd know you were a deserter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
They yes - they'd have took all me money - took all me money so would have worked for nothing. So I gave them the name - the first one that came to me mind was Sidney Smith. Yes. I've been Sidney Smith ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no. I had to keep me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When were your born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The twenty-ninth of April 1889 - at number eight Seaton Street at Hampstead Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well, God Almighty knows, we shifted so many times - we - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you remember moving from that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Well I'll say no - keep very - I'll tell you why. That year - I think it was 1895 if my mother was told me - they - run you in the streets - the - er - what do you call them people that throw you out of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The bailiffs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Who? The bailiffs - they put all the people out - and put all their furniture in the gutter - and the time of it was - you know - you - I don't remember it but - that was the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And do you remember where you moved then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Moved then? Yes. Number nine Whitlow Street, Kings Cross Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you move again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. A lot of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you remember where you went then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Whitlow Street to Kings Cross. Twenty-four Warren Street, Tottenham Court Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember when that was? What year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Around about - 1907 or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And where did you move after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I went on a training ship that year I did. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how long did you stay on this ship - how many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
I stayed on there round about three years and I was signed on as an apprentice in a sailing ship and I went round the world and round the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what year were you signed on as an apprentice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 About 1908 or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember why your family kept moving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Because - well - I'll tell you why - me mother had - there was John, Andrew, Bill Harry - Frank, Barbara, Maggie, Charlie and Olga - there was nine of us. My mother had to go to 
work to keep the nine of us and I've been to the place where she worked since - it was in a restaurant in Kings Cross there - she used to work at four o'clock in the morning to round about ten o'clock at night. And she used to get just enough to pay the r
e
nt and - and she used - er - bring the leavings and that home for us. You got no relief in those days. No relief at all. But of course I remember round about that time - when a working man was walking, if he was walking anywhere around - the Park Lane or 
the back there or Mayfair or Grosvenor Square he was arrested for loitering. A working man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many years were there between your brothers and sisters, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Jock was the eldest. I told you in rotation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That was how they came, and how many years between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh about eighteen months between - yes - be round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When he was born? Oh God Almighty - he died - he was about forty-four when he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh very - I was only a youngster then - er - we was living in Whitlow Street then - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you were very small were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - very small - very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So he'd have been about forty when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - Nairn in Scotland. He was a soldier in the 71}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 st}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753  - 46 \{BLANK\} My mother came from Edinburgh. Edinburgh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you're a true Scot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, I am - I was the first born in London. Well me mother ca
me down - and me father came down to London in 1889 - it was the beginning of the year - we were in London three months - me mother was in three months when uncle Harry came on the tour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And your father was a soldier then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, yes, he.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was he a soldier all his life?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - he was a private - private in the Home light Infantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he have any other job before he was a soldier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no, not as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. When, - when he came to London he worked at Maples - Tottenham Court Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 He was a foreman packing case maker. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he do any part time jobs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, he worked all the hours God sent him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And so he worked in Maples from when he came to London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 'Til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And he died in - when was it you said he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 About 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 He was never out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh, I don't know. Couldn't tell you that, could I? She died in - just before this last war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 About 1938?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - seventy-four she was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And where were you in the family - in age - were you one of the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, Olga was the youngest - she died. We were all alive when me mother died. I was the only one that worked to keep her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you the second to youngest or the third to youngest, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I told you - Jock, Andrew, Bill and then Harry - that\rquote s me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you're fourth - you were the fourth one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Fourth - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - she worked in a laundry - in Edinburgh, as far as I know - that's all she would tell us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And she worked after she was married you just told me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh no, me father done all that. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 She didn't do any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no. You couldn't get part time jobs in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember how many rooms there were in the house in Warren Street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Twenty-four Warren Street - two. For all of us - yes - two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That was eleven of you there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Mine. No there were ten - Jock, Andrew, Bill, Harry, Frank Charlie, Pat, Maggie and Olga.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And your mother - ten of you in two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Two rooms - oh well Jock was away - he was away at sea - we never saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Couldn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How could she pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of things did your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of things did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I mean looking after the children and cleaning and all the usual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 We had to look after ourself. She went out to work to get money to pay the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh she did go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Some place - sometimes - we had to move quick - couldn't pay the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What work did she do to earn the money to pay the rent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the kitchen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get on with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All righ
t. Always have. I was the ugly duckling you see but I was the only one that played the game. Yes I was. The only one - they all got married and they left me and my mother like - the Lord left the Jews.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was the washing done at your house or did your mother send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 She done washing for other people if - if they sent it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And she did it all at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Mend our clothes? Of course she did - there was nobody else to mend them was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she make clothes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No, no. Oh no, we wore one anothers cast offs. Oh we - wore noth - practically noth - wore nothing - no shoes - went about bare footed - good God Almighty - yes. Went about barefooted. When I was a kid - we us
ed to go to - different coffee shops - they was coffee shops in those days not cafes - coffee shops - and stand outside with a bag waiting for the girl who was in the serving to something to call us in and give us the leavings. Collect the leavings. In th
o
se days a man worked on the railway as a driver - if he drove a one horse van his wages was nineteen shillings a week - if he got married he drove a pair horse van - that was twenty-one shillings a week - doesn't matter how children he had anything - and 
t
here was no - well if you went to the relieving officer for any relief they gave you a big loaf of bread and you had to - you had to have a paper to wrap it up in - you had to put it under your arm - me mother did - and walk along - so that everybody in t
he street knew that you had been to - the Parish \{ILLEGIBLE\} - that was in those days. Horrible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Before your father died, when you were a very small boy, do you remember him helping your mother with jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, he never did do - no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, never.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he do things like decorating or repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he ever do anything for you, like bath you or dress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Nothing at all - left all that to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any jobs when you were a child that you had to do regularly at home to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Out to work. Well I went out to work when I was thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But when you were much smaller at home..........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 We wasn't indoors. We used to walk the streets all night at times. I remember - when - the -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753  er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
 - Salvation Army bloke - Loofe was his name and Doctor Barnardo - used to go down the mews's and the stables and lift up the tarpaulins to see if there was any derelict children under. I want to tell you something. Now you can
 verify this - what I'm telling you - you can go to this place tomorrow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12075913\charrsid14709753  - do you know - er - Southampton Road- do you know Guil}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 ford Stre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12075913\charrsid14709753 et - go down to the bottom of Guil}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
ford Street on the left - half way down on the left-hand side you'll see a big playgro
und for children - the foundlings - at the gate you'll see a big playground for children - the foundlings - at the gate you'll see a kind of a pouch - like - oval shape - and it looks as if there's been water in it for dogs - read that copper plate on the
re and see what it says.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What does it say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Do you know what it's for. Every morning the people that was in the foundling hospital there - they used to come out and put fresh straw round the door and women used to leave their unwanted babies in th
ere. Now that's hard to believe isn't it. All you have to do is go down there tomorrow and have a look - and sure to God made Eve and Adam you'll see that there. It's hard to believe isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well no, because I've heard people say it was very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh it's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did the older children help the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, - we all helped ourselves - we had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They didn't look after you in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. 121
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Not when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no, any time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - I already told you didn't I - room to go to bed to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You shared the bed did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 We had five of us in bed at one time. That's when we had a bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where would your mother sleep - would she sleep with the other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes. With the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about if you had a bath - did you ever have baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't remember. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about clean clothes and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh we had 'em I suppose - ooh they were ragged - ragged - it was horrible in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were did you eat your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Meals? I don't think we had regular meals - one time me mother used to - er - send 
us out for - er - two pen'ort or three penn'orth of bacon bones - from these shops where they - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Grocers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Something - yes - I don't - somewhere where they deal with bacon - and she used to make pea soup - another time we'd go down - up to Ma
rylebone High Street to the butchers - I remember it very well - Drews and Craddocks - buy three penn'orth of pieces and we had - then we had a feast that day of course - stew - but when me father was alive we fed good 'cos mother used to give you some po
rridge. She used to buy seven pound of fine oatmeal and seven pound of course oatmeal and the people who sold it -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12075913\charrsid14709753  I think they're still alive - M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 elhuish's their name - she used to put all the plates on the table - soup plates - and fill each one with a pla
te of porridge, scoop a spoonful out of the centre and turn it over and put a little golden syrup in each and that was our breakfast - you'd say 'I've had enough mummy' 'eat the rest' 'I can't' 'well you get nothing else' well we didn't get any bread and 
margarine if we - so we ate that. The time - we really did well when me father was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And after he died was it.....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 After he died - oh we had nothing - we had nothing - we had to get pieces from other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you didn't have a regular breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. Regular breakfast - didn't know what breakfast was. I was brought up the hard way. Forty years on the high seas is - er - I was having a pint with a man once down the West End - I was in - er - off Regent Street there in a posh pub -
 I was talking a fair amount - riots in Eire - and a chap said 'can I join in' and I said 'yes what do you want' he said 'I'd like to listen to you' he says 'you seem well educated' Well I am educated. He said 'you must have went to a good school' I said 
'
I went to the finest school in the world - hes says 'you wasn't at Oxford?' I said 'no, nor Cambridge, nor Eton or Harrow' I said 'but it was the finest school I went to' he says - I knew I'd got him there he said 'what school did you go to' I said' the s
chool of experience, that's where I learned everything - I knew nothing before that - since then I've learnt an awful lot. Terrible. That's wh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8414243\charrsid14709753 ere I lived it all. I've travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 ed the world over and over again and, this might be hard to believe, I was bos'um of
 a twenty-four thousand tonner - a big ship in those days - I had to boss the crowd of men and your strong-arm men - get them all in tow.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And probably through having a tough childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Even though it was very hard in tho
se days do you remember - did your mother ever manage to give you anything different on Sundays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she make anything - jam or fruit pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, no. We 
had no such thing as fruit. We used to - mark, some of us used to trot round to Covent Garden - and what they call pick-ups - it was tough in those days it was. There was no alternative either that or starve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother buy tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 There was no tinned stuff in those days - it was either all dried stuff or proper vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she ever keep any hens or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Only what we got from the coffee shop - what was left over, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many times a week would you say that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well three or four times a week I suppose - if we got any. Whatever people left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever get extra meat from poaching or nicking or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well er - poaching? Where could you poach round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Not poaching in that sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Thieving? Er - lifting - yes. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that you could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh that was a few - er - if there was anything she'd give it to us first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When your father was alive did he have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Oh yes. When my father was alive - my - he worked at Maples as I say, he used to come out there at lunch hour - or we called it dinner - and he used to 
go to a pub called The Orange Tree on the corner of Gower Street and sit down. My mother used to come from Warren Street with his dinner - a beautiful dinner in one - a plate on top of it and then - er - wait to - er - and she used to run all the way to s
a
ve a ha'penny on the bus it was a ha'penny in those days - and from Warren Street to Gower Street to give him his dinner. And the men used to say, his pals used to say - what was his name - oh I forgets now - he used to say 'Mr Ross, you've got a wonderfu
l wife' - bring him a hot dinner every day. He had it whether we did or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you allowed to talk when you were eating meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. We all used to be sitting in the corner in the floor there talking and me father was home - come home and - 
me father was a big man - reading a paper and he used to wear a cap. Well he'd - er - here us arguing a point and he'd take his cap off and - throw it across the - it would skim across and if it caught you on the nose it was terrible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 From what there was to eat could you choose what you wanted or did you have to eat every bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Every - anything of what we could get hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What would your parents say if something was left over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 There was never anything left over - there was never enough to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 If you wanted something like the salt did you ask someone to pass it or did you just wait until it was offered or help yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You'd get it yourself if it was to hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. There was never enough for a first helping - we was all hungry - always hungry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was your mother particular about things like the way you held your knives and forks and sat at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't - I don't remember ever using a knife and fork as a youngster. He mum used to say 'fingers before forks'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you'd sit on the floor and eat your food with your fingers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where would your mother and father sit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 At the table and chairs - they had chairs. They sat on chairs - two or three chairs, there - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Mother. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father ever carve or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. No. Mother done all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 She was very nice. Wonderful old lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When she was young and you were a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she show you a lot of affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - didn't show me any - did the others - did the others - I was the ugly duckling as I say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And she wasn't affectionate to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No, no, no. Nor was me father. It's a funny - I find it strange - when they used to say to me - when my mother died - when I living in Somerstown they used to say never mind Harry you'll always have luck with - you always looked after your mother - and by
 God it turned out true. Worth it - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was your father an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Very strict. Very strict.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So when you were little you couldn't talk to him easily? Was he affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Not to me - he had one boy - left home in fron
t of me - he served twenty-seven years in the army - in there a long time - well when he was a kid he was like a Little Lord Fontleroy, long golden curls - we used to come from Warren Road every day see, to cross - to Kings Cross Road to the Italian Ice C
r
eam shop - me father used to buy us an ice cream - and he used to - er - give me an ha'penny yes, Frank he used to take for a walk see, he was the favourite. Never, none of 'em ever thought of me - I was - I don't know what's wrong - I was a throw - out I
 suppose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your parents expect you to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't think they cared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they ever say you should hit back or not if somebody hit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well, if we went out - if we were out i
n the street and we quarreled - with another kid and we hit the kid - er - and their mother came to tell my mother - she - she'd give them a good wallpping - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be certain sorts of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Don't know what they thought. I - they thought how to get - try to live, I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Swearing? Oh no. Wouldn't allow us to swear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And if you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Get a walloping. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Who would do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Mother - father wouldn't - no. No - mother used to belt the living daylights out of us at times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many times do you think you got this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Me? Every time she saw me. I reckon I was - I was the villain of the piece I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father ever beat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Me father? No. He only hit one of us once - that was the next one in front of me. He done something - I don't kn
ow what it was - and he crawled under the bed and father come in and he picked him out like that - he was a very strong power-ful man and he hit him on the nose with his walking stick and his nose burst, you see, and afterwards he was very sorry. He told 
me mother he would never hit a boy again. That's the only time I remember him hitting anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Would you say that - do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - for stealing. Yes. Stealing, you see, little things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you feel about it when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh I don't know. I used to take it all in me stride I suppose.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - I learnt - all I heard - was 
after - was when I started travelling at sea - at sea. I learnt all my life on the sea. Yes - like - me traveling - that's where I learnt my life. Learnt nothing at school. When I was at school - I don't know whether it's still going or not - it was \{
ILLEGIBLE\} school - the - er - they used to tie me to the radiator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Who did - the kids or the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Mast - the headmaster - in the hall - tied me to the radiators in case I run away. Kids at school now have the times of their life. That's why I got put in the training ship - for not going to school - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you had a birthday was it different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Not to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You didn't get any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, I never knew what a present was. My uncle Frank - my mother's yo
ungest brother - came down from Scotland once to see us - well we used to sit out on the doorstep waiting for him to come out - and there might be four of us sitting there and he'd give us a penny between us - farthing each. If he give us a ha'penny - whi
ch was double each, we thought the world of him - thought we was rich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you think of anything you did together with your mother and father on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Father was always out Christmas Day. Yes. Me mother used to sit in a chair like th
is and we'd all sit - stay round her and she used to buy them - little tenet sweets - white sweets - with I love Flossie and all that kind of thing on 'em. She used to read 'em out to us and give us one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And that was on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I never had a toy in me life - never - I never knew what it was to have a toy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father ever take you out by yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - I think if he'd ever took me out he'd have threw me in the canal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You never went out with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never - with anybody. Nobody did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You didn't go on any outings at Bank Holiday or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - I was a throw out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Away? No money you know. We used to walk from Kings Cross to Hampstead Health and
 it was fun of the fair in happy Hampstead in those days different from now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Would your parents take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, on our own, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember how you used to spend Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Saturday? It was the same to us. Never different from one day to another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But you didn't go to school on Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Didn't go to school on Saturday - didn't go to school any day if I got the chance. I would run away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Anything special about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Nothing whatever - nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
So your parents weren't worried whether you played games or what you did on Sundays? No. Did your parents go to church or any place of worship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No. Oh, there was a man used to come round and - from some - man used to come round from some religio
us society and he used to say 'Mr Ross - you'd make a wonderful Christian' me father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But he didn't go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Or any place like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The only church he went to was where there was bitter in a pint pot instead of mild. He loved his beer I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What denomination were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Presbyterian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Both your mother and your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. That's very funny you talking about that - er - last - year before last - last year - I was in Ireland - in - my friend takes m
e over, you know, to his parents and his sister and they - are very - nearly to become a Catholic - they're all Catholics - and - er - this - his sister - May - she says - she calls me by Harry - Harry Ross - she says - er - where were you born Harry - an
d
 I told her where were you Christened and I told her in St Giles's. She says when were you baptised - I said oh blimey I don't know that I says, too far back. She says you weren't baptised in the Catholic Chapel were you? I says no so she says well you're
 
not a Christian. And I've every years I've been subscribing to them when I could afford it to the Catholic church there and to the Benedictine Monks and they thought a lot of me the people there and she said - when I told one person - Mrs Cooney never sai
d
 that to you, I said she did you ask her husband. Said I wasn't a Christian. So well I said blimey if I'm not a Christian I wouldn't be a Catholic at that rate. And you know - her mother died four year ago and she was ninety-three and she thought the worl
d
 of me - her mother gave her that when she was a child - and May was sixty-four now and she gave that to me when she first knew me - when she first came over here twenty-five years ago and I've always had it with me. A souvenier - a keepsake. That's what 
I think of religion - I don't believe in it. I don't believe in it. I seen so much of it in different parts of the world - so much of religion that honest to God - I say honest to God - I don't say - look I'll tell you this ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any musical instruments - did anybody in your family have a musical instrument at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was there anyone who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sang? Good God no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever make any music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Nothing whatever. We was all gone poles
 apart. We all used to go our own way. We all used to go to different - in the streets - go our own way - anything where we - where there was grub. We used to go to Euston Road - Fitzroy Street - about - five or six shops past Fitzroy Street there was a s
o
up kitchen - and there used to be queues of men there - hundreds - waiting for them to - for them to - someone to pass them tickets and give them one each - each ticket cost three ha'pence - you'd go in and get a big bowl of soup and a chunk of bread or a
 big bowl of rice and a chunk of bread - we used to go there - time when it was open.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That would be when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Get some grub - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever have any books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Books? My mother had a book which she gave 
to me - I took it away with me to sea and I carried it for years. That was Robbie Burn's poems. And there was one thing she pointed out to me - she said you always remember this boy. I said what is it mum. Excuse me I can't speak fluently I haven't got me
 
teeth in, they're over there. And this - when - the only time Robbie Burns was caught out was by a cotton sweeper - 'course they used to sweep the roads - the pavements with a gutter - and stand with it like that - to - anybody pass - anybody give them a 
h
a'penny or a penny. Well he was crossing the pathway and he see this crossing sweeper - and he says - seeing then taking your broom and let a body pass - the crossing sweeper turned round to him and said you silly arse can't you pass between the wall and 
I, and the only time Robbie Burns was caught out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Newspapers? Oh I got papers for three or four weeks. Ha'penny a time then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But you didn't have any in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Me father used to have the News of the World.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh me father used to buy Strand magazine. Yes. He bought that while he was alive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember your mother or father reading at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, only the newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Or to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember there being a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Funeral? Me father's funeral. The only funeral I remember - on me second brother - second eldest brother Andrew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember your father's funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What was it like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
I tell you, look, I'll tell you this. E - I was in charge of a fire party in the city - when I left the sea you see, I had two brothers playing up at the time, and I got this job as - in charge of a fire party in th
e city. And the men come round to me - I know - early in the morning I was walking around and I see a man sitting outside on a heap of sandbags - and it was me second eldest brother and he said he was doing his fire-watching duty - and I says to him I say
s
 look - I gave him a couple of pound because I thought he could do with that - I says - er - Andrew I says I've got a good job on this weekend I said I've got to shift a lot of machinery I says, and see me tonight and when the contract - when I sign the c
o
ntract I said I'll give you a fiver. In the evening a man come round to me and he says - er - are you Jack Ross' brother? I says - yes - they call him Jack you see - I says yes - he was working for Prince Farr in those days - I said yes. He said I've got 
some bad news for you - he told me me brother was killed - the machines fell of the - off the lorry onto him - crushed him. I helped to bury him - I don't remember anything about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You all went to your father's funeral though did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you wear mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. I know - all I know is that Maples - every man in the works - married man - gave a shilling to help me mother - er - two shillings to help me mother and every single one gave a shilling. That's exactly it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did any of them come from Maples?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. They was only - of course Maples was only a couple of shops in them days, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. When we were out - when me mother - when me mother wanted shopping it was half a pound of sugar or quarter of a pound of tea - a pound of margarine or something like that - always something to eat though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you didn't go to church and you didn't go to Sunday school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father take any interest in politics do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. He used to go Sunday to listen to the speakers - down at the Arches at St Fancras there - that's where he used to take the y
oungest from me - brother Frank - but I don't think he knew anything about politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You don't know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. He was a royalist - he was - ooh - I remember the time - when I'd take me shirt off and fight 'til I dropped for the Que
en. Not now. I got the King and the Queen tattooed on me chest - in the Southampton Road there. That's how patriotic - I was - and I even done me share didn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And your father was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - we was all patriotic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about your mother - did she have any particular views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. No. No - we had all our time to try and live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember your mother or father voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No. The general election? I remember when I was a youngster - when we was living at Kings Cross
 - there was a man - you know - er - Judd Street - well go down there on the left hand side you'll see a block of flats called Jessel House - well there was two men in those days - one was Harris - Labour and Jessel was a Conservative - and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 This was when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes. And they all taught us to sing this - vote, vote, vote for Mr Harris - Jessel's knocking at the door - Mr Harris is a man and we'll help him all we can and won't vote for Jessel any more. When I was a kid. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In s
ome places at that time some men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers - do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. People didn't own their houses in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But he didn't feel under any kind of pressure to vote in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And he wasn't a member of any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, he wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time? How did your mother spend her time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sitting indoors. Sitting indoors all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh - he used to go out and see his friends and have a pint in a pub I suppose - tuppence a pint - those days. I'll tell you the pub. Corn
er of Whitlow Street the Butchers Arms - the Builders Arms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When your father got home from work in the evenings what time was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I - used to get home round about six o'clock I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I can't - remember that. I know he was never home Saturday and Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he go to any clubs - he went to the pub - but did.....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. No. If - if you want to know something about a pub - the East End - I'll tell you. It was - er - a man walking along Whitechapel Road - er - Commercial Road - up on the left hand side there was a pub called the Gloucester - bel
onged to - er - that blooming firm now - brewers - a long name - Charringtons - and he see this man walking along - he see a first come out of this pub - hit a woman - knock her right out. And he helped the woman up and the fellow tried to give him one. T
h
e Guv'nor of the pub called him back - he said 'you come back and have him'. She said - his wife said 'don't let him in here' she said 'he aint having something 'til he's got a couple of bob'. That man that helped the woman up he looked at the pub and he 
s
aw Charringtons - do you know what he said - he was a Charringnton - 'cos Charringtons had three sons - even now. He said 'if that's how my father got his money - I'm finished. That was the man that opened the East London Missions. There you are. Purely t
hrough the fight - when he saw that. I remember that very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you a child when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother ever go out with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sport? No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he ever go racing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never had any money to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So if they were sick or a funeral they wouldn't have anything put by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Nothing whatever. Because in those days - if you had a shilling - shilling - say if you had sixpence - you could take your girl out theatre - theatre of varieties - tuppence for her and tuppence for yourself up in the - the gallery you know the gods. Tupp
ence each and the two pennies that was left you could buy two banburys or cakes or - er - one banbury between you and a bottle of pop between you - for tuppence - tuppence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I didn't get on with any of them at all. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was there any one that you felt close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Close to? Yes - the eldest one - the one that went to sea - he was the one - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was that Jack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 John.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 As a child who did you play with - your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Any neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No neighbours. We were always separated - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the street. On the pavement or in the gutter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What games did you play - do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Ho - oh the bosun's
 - the bosuns mate was a jolly old cockney - jolly old cock was he - he played outside on the starboard watch with the people all in jail.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You used to sing that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes, yes. Hopscotch and things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you remember any other games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. Piggyback and all that kind of stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 We were never clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you free to play with anyone that you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I suppose so. My father used to say - and a - bla
ck going along the street and we - should have hung him out on a Spanish flag - that was me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they ever tell you there were some children you couldn't play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never, never, never
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were there any sort of youth organisations that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - I wasn't - the boys may have done - I never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you spend your free time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Scrounged round the streets. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any hobbies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Hobbies? No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Only fleas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Anything I could lay me hands on I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - with a bent pin - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Miles and miles and miles - all along Tottenham Court 
Road - Oxford Street - all along the gutters. And - yes - walked to Hampstead - far as Crouch End, Barnet oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever do any bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never knew what a bicycle was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you take part in any sports when you weren't at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Boxing when - not at school - no - after that - I done a bit of boxing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But not when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you go to any theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Theatres? Yes - the Sadlers Wells when it was a theatre of varieties 
- when two brothers kept it - Sam and Will Palowski - well it was tuppence up in the gallery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you used to go to Sadlers Wells?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And did you ever go to any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never heard of any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Any music-halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sometimes
 we used to go to a magic lantern - it was local. Magic lanterns - that's before cinemas. When we saw - down Kings Cross Road - when we saw a motor car coming along we all used to cheer like hell because it - was so rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever have any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Never. We never got any - but if we'd ever have had any pocket money - I never had any pocket money in me life - only what I've made myself - what I've.....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did anybody ever give you an odd copper or a ha'penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Only once - me uncle had a van - come down from Scotland - give us a ha'penny each - but that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What would you do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Buy a house. Farthings worth of all-sorts. All sorts - that's all mixed - you know, the leavings of things - sweepings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did anybody outside your house ever give your mother a hand to look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Never. And - in any way - shape or form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So what would happen if your mother was ill or she was confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I never known her be confined to bed - not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about when your younger brothers and sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, I've never known her to be ill - me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, not ill - but what would have happened when your brothers and sisters were born - how would she manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh God Almight
y knows. She had another sister in London - she died many years ago - I - sent me mother - she said well - see - I used to send me mother - a lot extra money for - er - to go up and see me Gran in Scotland - she was ninety-eight when she died - and - er -
 me mother's sister - Elizabeth - came round to see her in Whitlow Street - no in - we was living in Euston then - she dropped dead in me mother's house. And me mother had to bury her - she couldn't - she didn't go to Scotland that year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did she come round regularly, your mother's sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any other relatives living nearby - any of your father's family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Me father - me mother's eldest brother was - er - had - er - had two daughters called - ladies of the r
ace - champion swimmers - he was the champion world champion swimmer, years ago, I remember - oh yes. And me mother's - me mother's - me father's brother was - doctor of Carlton Towers for twenty years - in Edinburgh - Old Leeky they used to call it or so
mething.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you didn't have anybody else living nearby you except for your mothers sister? Did your parents have any friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Friends? Only neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't know. If we went out I suppose. Me mother liked a glass of beer now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And she'd go out for it would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, yes. 'Course it was tuppence a pint then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they have the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Same friends? No, no, no. Me father used to go with his own mates, you know, years ago - his own mates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Did your mother have any particular friends of her own that you can remember? No? Were any of the friends invited into the home - say your father's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. We were too poor to invite anybody in. The home was like a - oh it only had a few sticks in it - as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did anybody ever call in without being invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Any neighbours - would neighbours drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - very seldom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - no me 
mother never used to only when she went to see me aunty like - her sister - very seldom. She had - er - a hell of a job to try and make ends meet and get the rent and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusement - what d
o you think your parents did when they got together - in the little spare time that they had - if they got together with their neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - no, I don't believe anything about them making mu - their own amusements - I don't believe any of that. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 It wasn't true for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No, no, no. I don't believe in any of that. They all had - all they used to do was - people that could afford it would go to a magic lantern or a mothers meeting or anything like that in the neighbourhood. There wer
e no other amusements. Go to the horse show at Regents Park when that started or things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 A lot of people divide people into social classes or groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one sort of class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Now I - I always knew - always knew that we were of the lower order - the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what other classes were there when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 There was only the rich and the poor, that's all. In my esti
mation. Just the rich and the poor. And everybody used to - er - bow to the rich in those days. I didn't - never bowed to anybody. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And poor people were - what sorts of trades and things like that were poor people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - everybody was poor in those days - as far as I know - we weren't - only people we used to congregate with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what about people who were very rich - what sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never used to go near them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. When me father died me mum - me mother never had much control over us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh we were told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was there anyone you remember you called Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sir? Yes, all me life until I learned to stand on me own feet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So when you were a child you'd call .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Oh yes. When I became a man - when I travelled round the world I knew that I was as good as anybody else - I had no superior.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But when you were a child do you remember anyone ever showing respect to your parents by calling them Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. I was - I'm no communist. Oh good God Almighty, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You just think you're as good as the next man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Exactly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
When you lived in these various district round London round Euston and places like that who were the most important people who lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well - I - no they were all working class - working class only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about the shop keepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Shops were very poor - you could buy a ha'porth of this or a ha'porth of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And the people who owned the shops - were they poor too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about clergymen and teachers - did any of them live near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of people would you say used to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Well the middle class people was the only ones that went to church - those who tried to show off on a Sunday - in their Sunday best - they were the only people who go to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was there a chapel near where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Near where we lived? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Would you say that all the people who lived near where you did who were poor people like you were do you think they had the same standard of living or were there different groups?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, they all had the same - it was all - get what you can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think some families were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The only thing I know is this - that on the - er - as regards with going to church was - near Christm
as time all the people - the women that used to go to the mothers meetings - was to - follow it up until they got - another hundred - weight of coal or whatever it was - they used to give it the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13912431\charrsid14709753 m Christmas time or a small parc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 el - outside of that - nothing - they - they never went only because when they got something free.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember there being any distinction between craf}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13912431\charrsid14709753 tsment}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753  and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Craftsmen was looked up to. Yes. They were tin gods. Specially fitters Fitters. They were all trained craftsmen, they was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of fitters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - well - engineers - fitters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They were looked up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, oh yes. They were looked up to all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different classes and groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. They all - my mother - all she done was to try and please me father. While he was alive she looked after us the best way she could.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think your mother thought of herself as being the same sort of person as your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they both come from poor families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't know me father's family - they came from north or Scotland. Nairn - near - about three and a half miles from Inverness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think it was possible when you were a child to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. They were too ignorant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember when you were a child anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady - did anybody ever use those terms?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Only - only that missionary m
an who used to come to see me father. He used to say 'Mr Ross, you'd be a fine christian and you're a real gentleman'. It was a good thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about your mother - did you ever hear her talk about anyone as a real lady or gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No
. When I was a kid - when me father was alive - people used to send us down from Scotland a big hamper with all goodies in - er - until me father died and then it stopped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Why did they stope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well - I never had contact - I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They were your father's relations were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes. I went up to see them - in Edinburgh I saw two - these two ladies of the lake and - that's 1916 - in uniform - Naval uniform - yes. And they thought they was going to see a little sailor boy - they wer
e surprised. Yes - they said we have something up in the cupboard there - they pulled out a bottle of whisky - they said we never take this but we keep it in case of accidents - you'll have to have one. I remember giving - me mother told me to take a litt
le we drop of whisky to me granny and I took her up a little bottle.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was this in 1916?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No a pint bottle - yes. And - er - I give her money - I give her eight half - crowns - of course she went blind you know - she was feeling round and counting 
them, I remember her saying it's all muckle laddie it's all muckle - that means it was too much. I told me mother and me mother started weeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Policeman? Blimey they were all over - used to walk round in pairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you think of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Think of them? We all used to - shout - and we used to run.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you were naughty would your mother or father say they'd call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Me father used to say find that chopper - bring me a chopper - cut our - cut our heads off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well they were the bossed - they used to knock you about. Terrible yes. The policeman in those days used to have - wear black gloves
 - woolen gloves and in the fingers of them - well they never had them on - in the fingers of them they'd have little marbles - and if they see anybody misbehaving - a youngster - crossing the wall - cross the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They'd hit the kids across the ear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were the houses that you lived in rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Rented, yes, yes. Paid rent - in every house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. You can't afford to pay, you hid, when they come marching down the street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Your parents had a big struggle to make ends meet didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you think about it when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Didn't think - all the whole time - get something to eat - nick something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever think about your mother having a lot of difficulty, did it never bother you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. Always trying to live. But I remember I used to steal sweets in Warrant Street - there's a big show-room there now - used to be a little shop and their name was Smith - funny I used to go in there and buy something f
or me mother and me hand used to creep up and steal a lump of coconut cake and she told me mother. Mother belted the living daylights out of me for it. Yes. We used to go away from home - walk the streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Because you were frightened of going home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was your father ever out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never. Never. Oh he was good to me mother - he paid her her money all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever get any help from Guardians or from ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Oh - when we was living in - Whitlow Street - we was -
 the way I can describe this is - you go along Judd Street on the lefthand side is the - the luxury flats and the street down there - I think it's called Sidmouth Street - on the right hand side was a big Presbyterian church - few of us was playing outsid
e there as kiddies and we all had new shoes on - new boots on - never had shoes in those days - boots -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was this when your father was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Father wasn't - no me father was dead then - me mother had bought them with some money she'd got - the wi
dows - er - Scottish Widows Fund used to give her a little bit now and again - and a lady come along - or a woman - she said she was going to buy us new shoe - bootlaces - and she took our boots off and - er - stole 'em and opposite there's a big eye hop 
- place -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Moorfields isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Used to be - er - police station - Hunter Street - police station -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 It's still there isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Is it? Well they took us in there and I remember right to this very day - when they found out where we l
ived - they took us round - I remember the woman putting a jelly baby on - you know, on the coppers head. Shall never forget that. The woman sold our shoes - and the police gave us shoes - and they were standard - police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They gave you shoes the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Those boots yes. She had to go through the magistrates - ooh took a lot of fuss and they gave us a pair each and stamped on them was police - so's they couldn't be pawned, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you mind having that stamped on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh - I couldn't read it them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever given lessons by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't remember - six or seven - five or six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you first started what time in the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what time would you go back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Two o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And stayed 'til what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Half past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And that was right from when you first started school? You never went just in the mornings?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh a few minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, I used to go to school on me own - the - I was the only once a
t this school. Because the other schools wouldn't have me. I used to run away. What do they call it - hopping the wag. Yes - playing hookey - hopping the wag.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you run away from the first school you went to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Always did run away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many schools did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
I went two schools I remember. Prospect Terrace School and the other one was in Scarot Street in Euston Road - that's when we lived in Warren Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How long did you go to the Prospect Road School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Couple of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And then you went to the other school 'til you were thirteen.?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Stoner Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you think about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I didn't think of them either - and I didn't like 'em - Mr Newman in particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Which school was he at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
In Stoner Street. You see, he give me - when I run away from school and mother brought me back - he used to give me six with the cane - held your hand out like that - one - two -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What each hand alternately?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes. I remember - when I - was first sent to the training ship - there was a man there - a schoolmaster - Mr Ferguson - and who - he was spiteful - used to cut me hands off. Now about - might have been twenty years after - I - I was going
 up to Tilbury to join a ship - I was bosun of a ship over there and I saw this man in uniform in the train and he kept looking at me - he says your face is familiar - what's your name. Sidney Smith. He said are you sure. I said no Harry Ross. I knew it. 
I
 said yes you knew it, I said look here, I said, I said it's a pity you're an old man now - I says - otherwise I'd squeeze you through that blooming window there, I said, how cruel you were to me. I never forget that - I'll remember that to my dying day -
 Mr Ferguson - he was a Scots man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you were at school did the teachers tell you that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - I don't remember anything about that - I - I never even listened to them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They didn't go on about manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh they had to tell you all about that - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh that was the main things - punctuality - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They didn't teach you that - not in those days - no. Because you
 see, taking the social side of it - teachers were only allowed to teach you the three R's because if you got too important - you learnt too much you was - rebel against it you understand what I mean, that is - been - what I learnt all through life.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Teach you just enough and not ....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 If you did something the teachers were cross about what would they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Report you to the Headmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what would he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 He'd give you so many cuts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was that at both schools the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. All - all these schools were the same. They were very cruel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And did they treat the girls the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't know - I didn't know - I never been to a girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of things would you get reported for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Talking. Hitting somebody or - or knocking about like that - playing about or not coming in early or running away from school. I was always one for running away from school - I didn't like school at all - I detested it. I detested it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your parents show any interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. My mother didn't. Father didn't care either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They didn't ask you what you'd done at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Ever go and meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did the other children at your school come from the same sort of homes as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Of course they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I think so - the only thing I remember about school really is this - in one sch
ool you paid three ha'pence a week - in our school you paid nothing. That's all I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you pay for either of your schools?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No not in our school we didn't have to pay - that was in London School Board - L.S.B. It was on the school board
. There wasn't no LCC you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were there any gangs or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Gangs? Oh yes - we used to go round in gangs - breaking windows and things like that. Stealing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And were there any children who were left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Left out? What do you mean - left out? Oh good gracious - yes. They used to say I'm not playing with Ross'. Well, we was villains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You were thirteen when you left school were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I was thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the chance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I wouldn't have gone ever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. I owe it to experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Because I've seen everything in this world - I've had years - I was out in Africa - 
America - Australia - China - Japan - all Canada and I've worked in most of the countries and I've learnt it through experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 From not going to school. Of course I did. I didn't learn anything at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 While you were at school did you have any part time jobs or any means of earning a little money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You said that you sold papers for a little while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I had - only of a night time you see give you about
 - give you - look - the papers was delivered to - er - High Street Bloomsbury and the man on a bike used to bring 'em you know - and he used to give them to the - er - paper stand and the bloke that had the paper stand - he trust you - he'd say don't do 
the hammers - don't drop them you see - used to give you nine copies - that's fourpence ha'penny - if you sold 'em he'd give you a ha'penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh - er - nine - ten or eleven. Star, Sun and Echo. Echo yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Every day was this, every evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Saturday and Sunday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, not Sunday. No Sunday papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So you got about a penny ha'penny if you sold the lot, what about if you sold seven of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - you got about - nine copies - if you sold nine copies you only got a ha'penny. They was only a ha'penny each.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What happened if you sold eight or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Take one back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you wouldn't get any money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you think that was unfair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Of course it was - unfair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you spend the ha'penny on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Sweets. Ha'porth - ha'porth of specked apples or something like that - we used - cheapest - the cheapest you could get - ha'porth of anything. Steal 'em if we couldn't buy 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you like selling papers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did it alter your attitude to school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. It didn't alter my attitude - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you were thirteen you left and went on a training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you tell me about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The training ship? Yes. Took me 
there - they put me in uniform - and read the riot act out to me and that was that. Me mother used to come down and see me now and again when she could afford - second Wednesday, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you have to do on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Physical jerks - learn nautical jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you learnt to swim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
I learnt to swim - oh yes. I learnt it - I used to try and sneak away - to escape. I jumped over the side - and near - further on there was what they call piers like - jetty - and I got between
 there - the boat shot round the other side and caught me coming through. I got twelve strokes with the birch then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You didn't like it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Blimey - who does. The birch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No I meant the training ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No I didn't - because you had to obey orders there see got to take a key and all that kind of stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What jobs have you done since the first world war - you were a sailor for forty years you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Seafaring all the time. Sometimes - I stopped ashore in America - sometimes in Australia and - few months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When did you leave the Navy - how old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I was in merchants - er - Royal Naval Reserve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When did you leave the Navy - when did you retire?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 We - when I left the sea you mean altogether. The war had been on about eighteen months I should think. This last war - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you do anything after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes. Now listen. I was in a ship called the Southpoint - one of Furness Witney's boats - and - the war was on of course - we was coming from Philadel
phia to London and a cruiser hailed us to 'what ship is that?' 'The Southpoint' 'Who's the Captain?' 'Captain Newne' What are you about or 'what cargo have you got?' 'Foodstuff - very goodstuff too'. He says 'I'm sending an officer and men on board to see
 
the damage'. He come aboard, he says 'You got any - er - Naval - Naval men or Naval Reservists here?' Captain Newne was a big headed son of a gun said 'Yes I believe that man's a Naval Reserve man' - this was me. I nearly threw a double six. Oh that was t
he first world war. I nearly threw a double, see. 'You a Naval Reservist?' I says no. And he asked me a couple of questions - he says you'll do - took me aboard their ship. Took }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461207\charrsid14709753 
me to Devonport - went into Devo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 nport - put me ashore there - they had a depot 
there and they found out I was a Naval Reservist - into a battle ship - aboard the HMS Bugler and went out into the North Sea then I had to go all through the war. I got - I got quite a few medals during that war - I got a life-saving medal and certificat
e
 and that was the fifth of October 1917 - that was in - er Glasgow - jumping over the side - I nearly - I might have got crushed to death. Between a cruiser I believe - to save a man - I got him out and he died. But it was a life-saving medal and a certif
icate you know. And then when I come home - about 1919 I gave them to me mother to look after - 'cos I was demobbed like then. And then I went back see, carried on and - right up until this world war -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You went back into the merchant Navy then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Y
es. They opened up these St Mary's flats - church flats in Somerstown, Euston, - er - Drummond Street. My mother - of course we lived there in Drummond Street, but they pulled our house down - my mother was the first tenant there - front floor, and - lets
 
see - this one I think - the last King. It was the first one - it wasn't the one that abdicated - he says - er - the police was there you know, the Queen come round and inspected these flats - the King like. Me mothers flat the most prominent one - 'Mrs R
o
ss' - and he looked round and he says to me mother 'Are you happy?' 'Of course I'm happy', the inspector or this Chief of Police whoever he was showing him, he says 'Are you happy?' he said 'It's only a little time'. Me mother says of course I'm happy - p
u
lled down the frayed letters and says here's a letter from your father congratulating me on having so patriotic a family - six brothers and two sisters in the forces. He looked at her - are you happy - yes. I just came into the - the - when he said it. I'
d just come home to tea and I'd had a few drinks you know - I wasn't drunk - didn't used to drink much in those days. Chief of Police pushed me to one side and out they went. That was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you do when you came out of the Navy altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Back - went back in the merchant service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But when you left the merchant service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Post war years - I - er - left that - the merchant service until this war you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you do after that - anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I went to work on t
he - er - L.C.C. Rest Centre Service. You know, looking after Rest Centres. And when that finished and - er - I got a job as a - in a cinema - in Leicester Square, Swanzig Neuf. Now.......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What year was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That's - ten year - twelve year ago 
- fourteen year ago it might be - yes fourteen year ago. I stopped there and they sacked a man because - the doorman because he had a - a bad back - he had a couple of days off so - I went to see my doctor on account of this one eye, see, and he said I re
c
kon you'll have to go to hospital - get me a - I went to me manager and told him I was - I wanted me cards - oh no, no. We want you to - you're all right. I said I've got to go to hospital for a week or - we'll keep your cards - your job'll be all right. 
I says no bloody fear I says if you sacked Jack - er - I'll have me cards so I had me cards. I come away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What were you doing at the cinema - were you on the door as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. I was attendant inside. Now - I went into Moorfield's - I was in 
there ten days and they discharged me - said they couldn't do anything for me but I wouldn't go blind. Then I got a job as assistant manager in another cinema - up here in the Hampstead Road - the Tolworth cinema - rough house - they wanted a rough man th
e
re. I was down there years until this eye went - I was seventy - two then - until this eye - I didn't know it had gone - I couldn't see much but I thought - we didn't open 'til four o'clock Sunday you know and the owner of the cinema came round and he say
s
 how's it Smithy? I said all right. What pictures showing? I says - er - it's this epic - Greek picture - where he - er - the that big bloke got stabbed in the eye - blinded - what do you call it - Ulysses. I said that one, he says ring 'em up. Rung 'em u
p and told them to put it on - that was about three o'clock. There you are. He looked at the picture - he said I wouldn't go blind. Nearly nine year ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You stopped working then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Couldn't see proper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Would you have preferred to have done anything else rather than be a sailor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Than be at sea? No. I was - my heart and soul was in it - either in sail or in steam and I was what you call a sailor not one of those with a round hat and white trousers - a sailor. Of course those blokes wi
th their three rows of tape they don't know the first thing about sailorizing. We in the merchant service - they call us the merchant navy now - we made all our own tackle - all our own gear and everything an I could - put a block in a canvass blindfolded
.
 I could rope and wind - all my time on the training ship. And his sail - the best man was a good sailor. That's how I became bosun - I was bosun for sixteen years - that's the boss of them all - sixteen solid years. I knew it inside out. I knew everythin
g
 there is - you'd be surprised. In sailorizing. And I can ask a Captain of a ship today where - of the ship is and he couldn't tell me. Nobody heard of a tabernacle only we sailors - sailing ships - and you go up the fore-mast there's a table up there - t
h
ere's a hole where you through - stand on the deck - on the - er - foretop - that's what they call the tabernacle. They've never got any - now to the present day - well in my day these was wooden ships and iron men - now its iron ships and wooden men. Do 
you know what you can do today - and one man - the bosun and all the rest will be charwomen - all they got to do is wash paint and scrub decks nowadays. You wouldn't get them to do it in my days - it was sailors - you had to be a sailor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you belong to any special trade union - was there any union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - the sailors and FIREMENS union all me time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you take part in any of the activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And the worst man I ever met in this world was a man that's 
dead now - God rest his soul - he was a C.H. - Companion of Honour - Havelock Wilson - he was our president - he sold us to the shipping federation to the masters federation. That's why we never got anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you do - what part did you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh went to all the meetings - our depot - Tower Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You led them all did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes, oh yes. I would never take a delegates job on though because - sailors - when they get their money - their wages - try and get their - union rates - like getting blood out of a stone. They wouldn't part with it - sailors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You think there is some division between workers and interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh of course there is - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Some people say that in those days long ago when you were first working th
ere was a division between trained craftsmen and other workers - did you feel that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Well they - they were - all inferior to the bosun. I'll tell you why - he used to give them their job and see that they done it. That was your job - you had to do it and you had to be a good man to give it to 'em - to run the crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 So when you were a lad did you fear the bosun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, I always worked with the bosun because I always took - I always tried to learn as much as I - seen as much as I could, see, bec
ause when they go - get into another port the sailors all to ashore and the first thing they do is get drunk - come aboard and kill the bosun. Well that night 3/8 I always used to dodge the column - see and in the morning - come aboard to make their order
s I carry on me steady that's the way. I said yes private - come on you crowd - outside - I wait for who I thought was the ringleader - now then - if you're as good man as you was last night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Going back to when you were a boy on this training ship would you say that having a full time job - did it change your attitude to life?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well it taught me to play the game and be a man. Being a sailor. Travelling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 It taught you all you knew in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All I knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can we go back to the time after
 you left school? When you went to sea. Did being away from home and being on a training ship - did it change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I only had me mother didn't I? No, no, I - I was always fond of me mother - always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what about your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Well - I got no time for any of them. They all got married you see and they left me mother - they didn't give her - any - contribute towards anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you spend your time off any differently? Did you have any time off on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 On the training ship? Only once they give me fourteen days leave. Me mother came and brought me and - I stayed at home. I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What about Sundays on the training ship - was that the same as any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sundays? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you were first working did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. You see, we started on these ships when I first - when I was - er - able bodied seaman - the first other than boyhood - you started day light to dark - that was
 your days work - but - your job was four hours on and four hours off from the time you left port to the time you got back. That's eighty-four hours a week. Four on and four off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you always sleep in the four off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sleep? Blimey - you was dea
d tired. Now - in this steamer - steamship - running across - to America - you worked day and night - rain, hail or snow. You worked all the time - all your four hours - and you never - specially with sail - if it was bad weather the old man would keep yo
u on deck all the time - stand by the ship - whether it was twenty-four hours or forty-eight hours or whatever it was. It was all hard work and do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When you did have any spare moments what did you do with your spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Go to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You never had any time for anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No. Not like in these days. Now they've got four hours on and eight hours off. Well they're gentlemen now - they've all got cabins. Do you know - what we used to do - have to do - time I first started - we had t
o take our own mattress with us - a sack of straw - blankets - we got not - supplied nothing by the ship - and most ships you was - got your rations made out to you. Now they got - ooooh - they feed like fighting cooks now. And you know - two pounds five 
a month was our wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That was when you'd finished at the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes - when I was an A.B. Three pound five a month - and now it's about sixty - five pound a month. More than that - seventy pound a month now. Blimey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How old were you when you finished the training? How many years did you actually train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 On the training ship? About two and a half years. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You'd be about sixteen when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you make any new friends amongst the other boys on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - not really - not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You didn't have any special ones at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No, no. I was always by meself - all the time. I - they gave a prize each year - I was the first one to get a prize - I got for naut - for navigation. It was a knife - a penknife - I've still got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In 1912.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
When we had the London Strike on - dockers - all the railwaymen and all the sailors and firemen in the merchant navy - we had a general strike - the first strike we had - they all went back a
nd left us out. Had to say to the firemen we were still on strike - they went back. I was told off for picket duty - I was living in dock Street there in the sailors home - I was only there a week in the sailors home out - the head of the - our branch - t
o
ld me to go across to Leman Street - the shipping federation - masters federation - they're trying to sign on a crowd for a ship - and it was just before ten o'clock and as I got round I saw the one that was - used to be a pal of mine and - I heard that h
e
 was signing on and he came out and I said did you sign on that ship - he said yes. I'm finished with him. Well I made a kick at him - I caught him in the ribs - and I see the police and I run - and I run back into Dock Street where all these men were lin
e
d up to get the - we was getting two and sixpence a week - er - strike pay - the cops run down the street after me and they was looking at the feet of all the crowd - they saw 'cos I yellow American's ball toed shoes on. High heels, ball toes - I bought '
e
m in America. That's how I got arrested. I got sentenced to a month in prison without the option of a fine, 'course if I'd been fined the union would have paid it but anyhow I got this month - I done fifteen days at Pentonville and then they transferred m
e to Wandsworth and I done the other fifteen days up there and my mother came on the morning I got out and got me in a cab and straight away home, I'll never forget that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What was it like inside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh dear - oh lor. I was picking \{ILLEGIBLE\} - jus
t like old Charlie Rose - and I used to pick it you see - and they took me up before the Governor - that was in Pentonville there - and he said 'Look here, Smith your name is?' I said 'yes, Sidney Smith'. He said 'look here he said 'you'll pick that \{
ILLEGIBLE\} two pound and a quarter per day or else you'll be on bread and water for the whole of the time you're in here.' Well I started picking it. I kept meself off it. I'll never forget it as long as I live - that was the first time I was in prison.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh - it - it was solitary confinement - all - by yourself you see - all the time. In the morning you got - I think it was half}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10843852\charrsid14709753  an hour walking round in a circl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 e or or - all diff - separated from on another, you know, in all diff
erent parts. Weren't allowed to talk or anything, oh it was horrible that was. When I came out of Wandsworth they gave me a card and it had a convict on the picture - I never forget it and on this card it had a convict with all the - that's where they got
 
the design from - where is it - see it - broad arrows. On this card it had 'the pawnbroker has got my clothes, the publican my money, and here am I after fourteen days. I'll never forget that. Well that's the only time I was in the jug. For - been pinchin
g
 like. 'Course I been - in America I was in the - er - Caliboso just for a couple of hours 'til the Captain of the ship sent an officer out to get me out. That was only for - er - drunkenness - 'course it was playing the game - it was down in San Francisc
o I think it was - in California.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Why were you sent to the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 For running away from school - because I kept running away from school - hopping the wag - playing hockey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many other boys were there on this training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In this training ship? Oh about two hundred and fifty. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you were thirteen and how long were you on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Approximately three years I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you want to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well they asked me if I'd like to go to sea an
d I said yes. Well I knew I'd get something to eat there I suppose. But I tell you on that training ship it was worse than prison.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother discuss it with you - that you were going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They told her - I was going, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Who told her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I suppose the authorities they had - the home office I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Can you describe a typical day on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 A typical day? The day I went on or any day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Any day - a typical day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes, yes. When we had a
 bath - they were like horse troughs in this barrack room and water in 'em and we was all - we all stripped naked and there was an officer sitting down in a chair and a man along side of him with a big tub of soft soap and as he went by he slapped a dollo
p on the top of your nutthere. And all every poor kid had a bath - that was all the gang of us - you washed his back and then turn round and he'd wash your back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was it cold or hot water?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Cold. Cold. Ooh no hot water there. We used to run barefooted then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 On the ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes. Always barefooted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the winter and summer - as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All the year round - yes. All the year round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What time did you have this bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What time did we have? About twenty minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, what time of day did you have the bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Around about nine o'clock I should think - after the first school lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What time did you have to get up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Six o'clock every morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Lift our hammocks up - stow 'em, and then start scrubbing down the decks - I - we all had big scrubbers like that - on our knees you know, our trousers up perhaps above our knees, in line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well - er - after that we had breakfast I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Biscuits. Hard biscuits - no bread - never had bread - biscuits and cocoa in the morning - about four ounces of biscuit and cocoa - the - old seafaring biscuits - you know - hard ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was the cocoa made with water or with milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Water - no milk. And the - er - we had our dinner - meat and potatoes - little meat - and teatime we had biscuits - and - biscuits and cocoa again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have enough to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Never. We could 
eat any - one another. No, never had enough to eat - was only youngsters you know, I think I could eat like a horse in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you do after breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well we had - physical jerks and school - the school was wicked though - the teac
her - I - two elderly men - and I could - teach them lessons - that teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And then you'd have your lunch would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Lunch? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you do after dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 More schooling. Ever - of an evening we used to have - er - prayers
 you know, all church prayers - no matter what religion we were - we were all bunched together. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how long did they go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh about - they went on for about half an hour. Sunday morning we went to the - we had church on the upper deck
 - Captain used to read - read that and then we had afternoon church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have to say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1034\langfe1033\langnp1034\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no, no, no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Not that. The mess - the mess - er - fourteen or fifteen in each mess I think - and the mess that got the clea
nest - you see they had a table to take out with iron thing on it. The one that had the cleanest table and stools - once a month got a cake between them - plum duff you know, something like that - once a month that was. We used - blimey you could eat off 
of the floor and - the deck - really white I never forget that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you were kept busy all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All the time yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any free time at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Any what - free time? In the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Just laid about
 the decks. Oh - er - once a week - we - once a week - once a fortnight we used to all get ashore and line up four deep and march from Purfleet along the country road to Avery and then back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how far was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 About a mile and half or two mile, I guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Each way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. And then walk back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And that was once every fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Once every fortnight. That was our outing. Once a month we used to go to a place called the Dipping. It was a big hollow in a field and we used to play games there. Play all different games there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you good at games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Only at boxing. Ooh I had to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You learnt that when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes. When I was knee high to a grasshopper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was your mother allowed to visit you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Me mother used to come down the second Wednesday in every month - second Wednesday in the month - not always about once every three months - she used to bring me a tin of milk - condensed milk - some biscuits and some sweets and a small bre
ad pudding. And a lot of the boys never had parcels you know - never had parents - I never forget they had - ooh look out for Ross' - he's got something nice - ooh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did they try and get it off you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I used to give some away you know but - I was greedy - more for myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well you were hungry weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Always hungry. Had one particular friend there his name was Arthur Goodhew - of course you had to - your parents had to pay for you like to the Home Office - I think it was two shi
llings a week - my mother could ill afford it - but this Arthur Goodhew only had one relation - that was his sister - and strangely enough she lived along Southampton Row in them flats on the left hand side past the Imperial Hotel - she was had up to cour
t
 because she wouldn't pay and the Magistrate asked her - asked the court there what she was - he said that she was a lady living in them posh flats and that - she was rolling in gold, I remember that - and he said how uncomfortable - me mum told me about 
it - she read it in the papers - how uncomfortable - rolling in gold. She was very - married a wealthy man, you know, - I never forget that - Arthur either - he was me pal there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what happened when she didn't pay up - did they take him away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No they made her pay. Oh yes, fined her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How long did your mother stay when she came down on the second Wednesdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 About an hour and a half - two hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the afternoon or the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. Wednesday afternoon. Second Wednesday in e
very month - I'll never forget it - and I said to - tell you my number - three seven forty-seven, I was - that was me official number in the - same as a convict had a number and - er - my number on the ship's company was one ninty-six and I was in fifteen
 
mess - that's imprinted there - and there's one word that's - one thing that was imprinted in my mind which I never forgave my aunt for - you know Battell Street - well past - past that and down on the - first pub on the right past Drummond Street - it's 
t
he Prince Arthour and I told - me mother said go round and see your Aunty - and I - I got leave you see - was on leave - and I went round and see me aunty - a little sailor boy, you know, in uniform and she introduced me to the other women in the pub, she
 says this is my nephew from the convict ship - I never forget that as long as I live - from the convict ship mind you. It was a training ship - they reformed you there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How often could you get away from the reformatory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What on leave? Oh accordi
ng to the Master - the Captain of the ship - you applied to the Home Office or the Captain of the ship. If you was a decent lad you got away once a year or ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How long for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Seven days. Seven days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you went back and stayed with your mother, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes. I never forget it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever allowed to wear your own clothers off the ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. Oh no. You had no clothes. What you went - what I went on the training ship with they burnt I suppose - they were only rags. 'Cours
e things were very bad in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any personal belongings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Nothing whatever. And when I left the training ship - all I had was that pen-knife what I got - my knowledge in - nautical knowledge.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Were you ever homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. No, never homesick - no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was there anything you missed about your life before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Anything I missed? Only freedom - that's all. That's all I missed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did your mother write to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - she always - she wrote to me once in a blue moon - it was only a ha'penny stamp in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Do you think being on the ship changed the way you felt about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, never. I loved me mother more then. Well she's the only real pal in the world I had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did going on this training ship change your attitude to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 It certainly did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well it taught me how to play the game and work - and it taugh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid738587\charrsid14709753 
t me to put my whole life in sai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 lorizing. 'Course I - they apprenticed me to a sailing ship - to the Alexandra of Aberdeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 That's when you left the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Yes. They apprenticed me to this Captain of this ship. I was two months - two years and eight months in her when I broke loose - I - see I run away from that ship - and I got into a big sailing 
ship - and I went to Australia in her and back to Australia. From Australia to - er - Calio and Itici on the west coast of South America - we load salt petre home to Falmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How long were you with that ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Two months and twenty-two days. Two
 years and twenty-two days. On the round voyage - two years and twenty-two days. And when I paid off of that ship - you can believe me that I never had a god-damn penny - I spent the few shillings I earnt from that ship to buy from the - er - slop-chest. 
All I got was from the elderly sailors - they had - what they call a tarpaulin muster and they collected four pounds ten shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh I must have been - that must have been round about 1910 I think - nine or ten - round ab
out nine or ten. I was a full blown able bodied seaman and the law then of the sea - if a man could hand reef a sail - hand reef and steer he was an able bodied seaman - after that you became - you was on a ship three years - done three years actual sea s
ervice you was an A.B. Able bodied seaman and I - I can blow about that - I was one par excellence. I knew the game inside out. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you meet children of a sort you hadn't met before, on the training ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no. I didn't take any notice of them - we were all the same I think. We was all ruffians.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And when you went home once a year did you spend your time any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No - just walking around. Go up Regents Park - Hampstead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any new friends then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get on the ship - the Alexandra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
From the training ship - they took me there. They took me up to West Hartlepool took me before - er - to the Captain - him and this agent took me to the solicitors commissioners of oaths and I signed the apprenticeship.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did I have to do? Anything I was told.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what sort of things was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well - work round about the decks after cook - in the galley and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What sort of hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All the hours God sends us. Oh there was no limit. Twenty-four hours out of twenty-four. Oh it was murder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sundays and Saturdays as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sundays and Saturdays and high days - and my pay was supposed to
 be this - five pound the first year - seven pound the second and nine pound the third - I didn't finish the third year. Now - the Captain told me straight, he says - when you want clothes - anything - you let me know. Well when they fitted me out to go o
n
to this apprentice - they give me two shirts and I washed them you know and of course you couldn't use much fresh water and I put 'em a draw - with a - and I put them in the draw buckets and put them over the side like that to rinse and the blooming shirt
s floated away with the tide and I had no shirt. No shirt - I had a jersey - I'll never forget that. I had it tought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you have any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Holidays? I never knew what - they - there was no holidays - no such thing as holidays. Not seafaring - no - not the seafarers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you were paid five pounds a year the first year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Seven pounds the second and nine pounds the third. I didn't finish the third year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I never got any of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No the first year you got five pounds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, I didn't get any of that. Never none of the seven either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What happened to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well the old man - he - used to give me different bits of clothes out of the stock chest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And that came out of your pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes. I got nothing - no wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get on with the other sailors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh I were all right with them. 'Cos I was very willing to work you see - I was a willing worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did they treat you - how did the Captain treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh you never spoke to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Who was the man who was immediately above you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Chief Officer - First Mate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh he was - he was a bit rough - he - he saw me smoking a cigarette and he belted me across th
e chops and knocked the cigarette out of me mouth - don't let me see you do that again. I said the others are smoking. He says yes he says but you smoke a pipe - he said smoke a pipe when you're a few years - and I used to smoke a little clay pipe then, '
course tobacco then was about three and sixpence a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you feel about the First Mate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I don't know - I got over him all right - he was - he was - he see I was a willing worker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you actually like doing the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 I did - I loved the work. Oh I loved sailorizing - yes - no doubt about that. In me heart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 After that you went on this next ship the Port...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Fort Jackson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you stayed on that for two years and twenty days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Two years and twenty-two days. Active.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And how did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
I applied for it - went aboard the ship. Ship Master said to me look mate - the first words he says to me - there was a coil of rope laying on the deck - he says - how many ends on that rope - how many ends to
 that rope? I said - and I knew there was a catch in it - I said three. What do you mean three? I says three. He says show me. I said there's one end and there's the other end -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 He says all right you'll do. Oh he asked me different ropes - he did - f
rom the foresail - lower foresail - upper foresail - lower topsail - upper topsail - lower gunsail - upper gunsail - lower royal - upper royal - no, single royals - and skysail. All the ropes all the sails and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What was your job this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Sailor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you have to do that was any different from before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Well, I had to do all sailorizing then. All on decks - stand-by and all that. When the orders - when the wind would change - take me pick at the wheel. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What hours did you work on this ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh all the hours God sent us. We always did in all the ships then.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But you must have had a little bit of time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well, you were supposed to be four on four off but - they took a particular interest in thi
s - just about - a quarter of an hour before your watch was up to go off - you had to take in sails or fetch some sails - keep you another blooming hour on deck. Oh-ho - crafty. In bad weather you had to stand-by all the time no going down below at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you ever have a Sunday or a Saturday off in this ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, not in those days - that's impossible.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you get a holiday with pay in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No, no. Get no holidays, no holidays tell you, no such thing as a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what did you get paid on this ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Two pound fifteen a month. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well, it was all right in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you give any of that to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 No. I never got .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Buying clothes and things. And I never started sending money to me mother until I started going in steam. Well I came home - of course me brother was working there at home - when I came home - I started going in steam ships and - er - when you went
 in a ship - you signed on a ship you could leave an allotment note or you could have a half a months advance straight away, see, and that's when I started giving money to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And on this ship, the Fort Jackson, how did you get along with the other sailors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Oh - liked it. There was every nationality under the sun in that ship. Blacks, Chinese - ooh the whole mixture - all the whole lot. Germans, Norwegians, Swedes Dago's everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was it still the first Mate who was above you in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh the - above us was the Bosun.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did he treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh, he wasn't bad - long as you done your work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All right. You see, in those days of sail if you pulled your weight you was a good man - 
if you tried to slack you got a hell of a dogs life. So the best thing was to play the game, you see, and I always used to play the game with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 After that you went into steam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Steam - steam ships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The first steam ship that you went on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 The first steam ship I went into ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Applied - at the shipping office. The Southshields I think it was. I think that was - that was a Belgian ship - a Belgian tanker. I done four months in her - four or five months in her - I left her and I went in British tanks - British ships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What were you paid in this first steam ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Then? Oh the money was good then. It was three pound ten a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Was that the same all the way through - for all the steam ships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Now it didn't go up until 1912 then we got five pound a month, you see. Yes. I had a laugh at one ship I was in - after the - it was just before the strike - I came home during the strike - was the Montrose - the ship that they had docked at Pitn
ey - and - when I got home they was on strike - that's how I got to get into trouble - the Montrose - I had three voyages in her I think - she docked at Pitney did her - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And you did send some of your money home to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh yes, yes. In the - in the English ships - since I started going in English ships. And I always went in English ships after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How much would you send her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 As much as I could afford. As much as I could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what would you spend the rest on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Clothes. Mostly clothes. I always looked after myself you know. With clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what was the bosun like in this ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Steamships - oh all right. Some were tough until about 19 - er - I came out of the - I was in this - one of the first 
British ships - I came out of her in - 1914 - three months after the war started - when I got picked up - and when I went back - when the war was over I went back in this ship - I joined and oil tanker - that was in 1918 - beginning of 1919 - end of 1918 
I
 think after the war I done half a dozen voyages in her - the Anglo Oil Company - and - they said I was such a good man and - didn't join the boat - I got bosuns job. And I was bosun right up until I packed up. And I've had some of the finest ships out of
 
London. I used to - then - in them days - you had a good - mate - had a good bosun he wouldn't worry about the crew he'd say all right bos' go and pick your own men. I used to pick me own crew. And I only had to look to a man and talk to him to know wheth
er he was a sailor or not - 'cos I was one. I prided myself on that - definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What did you actually do in the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 In the war? 1418 war. I was in - I was in a battle ship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you actually engage in combat ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - no. We was up 
in - 1914/15 we was up in Arch Angel. The lastiin Lawrence to get a Cunard cargo boat out. She was loaded with stuff for the Russians. And - er - we kept on blasting the ice and going out in as far as we could in Archangel - discharge the cargo onto the i
c
e and the sledges and reindeers took all the stuff away. I got - reluctant Silver Medal for Zeal and the ribbon of the order of St. Stanislauv. From the Tsar of Russia. And got permission by the King of England to wear them. That was before the revolution
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What was life on board like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
Oh it was all right. In the battleship? Well we only - er - well it was - in the morning we had to wash - about sixteen of us washed in one bowl - about the size of that basin there, 'course you wouldn't throw the w
ater away, you see, you couldn't get much water, you see, only snow and that. Got thirty feet of ice there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What exactly did you do on this battleship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 All the drill. Well if there was any extra sailorizing of course the - Petty Officer of my - 
er - I was in the quarter deck - on - red watch I think - he'd come and pick me out to do a lot of jobs - because he knew I was handy you see. Well I always got that 3/8 well I got that - when I left that ship I went into - an old liner the Oritava - and 
t
he - er - from the merchant men - before her - and the bosun was a merchant man but he was a warrant officer you see, like had 'em - me being Naval Reserve then - and he knew me and I knew I was the man for the job and he used to - one time there a was - 
e
r - a - our flag up the mizzen and it was fouled and they couldn't get it clear anyhow and nobody could get up there. The Captain - he was real Admiral Waite - he says send for that bosun - and the bosun up there - the chief officer up there - oh nine off
i
cers up there arguing the point and he says well he - the bosun says I've got a man that'll do it - he says - who is it - he said hard - hard case Smithie, see, used to call me hard case Smithie you see, 'course he told - er - a mess - er - whistle pipe a
n
d messenger 3/8 fethc that able seaman Smithie - that ex merchant seaman - up I went - up aloft. Can you get that down? I said yes all right. I got up there and she was rolling to beat the band - I got it down and got it clear - when I got down on deck th
e
 bosun gave me fifty cigarettes - a tin of fifty cigarettes and he got half a bottle of rum you know - for what you call a thank you - and he smuggled it to me for doing that job. No other sailor - no other - petty officer would - and we used to have to d
o that - and we had two hundred and forty - two hundred and eighty of a crew there in that ship.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What hours did you work on the battle ship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 On the battleship? Oh it was stand-by all the time - mostly. Plenty of guns to stand by we had twelve inch guns you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 But was it still four on and four off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
No, no, no. Not in the Navy. No, we all had to be on deck the same time and - er - in the afternoon they used to call - hands to stand by - you could get your head down and have a sleep - or used to say join the carpenters party. Measuring stools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How many hours would you have to get your head down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh as long - as until you were working or anything in sight or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Oh the Navy paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 And what was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Well, I couldn't tell you how much it was now - me mum used to draw half pay. I didn't draw much - it wasn't much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Did you think it was fair - what they paid you in the Navy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Christ no - never very fair. You see I h
ad - the only time I used to get anything was thanks was when I paid the ship off went we got down to Chatam and I was dodging the column and it was a Sunday morning you see and all the crew - the men in the old depot was on parade there - for Admiral's i
n
spection and - er - the Admiral was - was going to go the rounds and the order came up to find able seaman - find able seaman Sidney Smith. 'Course all through the ranks they couldn't find me - they knew I was dodging the column. Anyhow they routed me out
 
in the finish and instead of taking me up to the offices they took me down to the jug and put me in the jug. And this here - there was a - er - a two ring lieutenant - he was a chief of police - they called him Jonty Blow - he come down and he says to the
 
bloke in the jail there 'have you found that sailor yet?' And he said yes. Bring him out of there. He was mad with them - ooh he was going to put them in jug. He said that mans got to go before the Admiral. Well there I was - I didn't know what it was for
 
- I thought I was going - in for something bad - escorted up - the Admiral's salute and all - had a rostrum there. And able seaman Sidney Smith, seaman R.N. 6441A - yes sir. I am commanded by the Admiralty to present you with this lifesaving medal and cer
t
ificate for your - er - action on the river Clyde on the fifth of November 1917 - a medal, you know, a bronze medal and scroll. I said well - do you want any requests? I said - yes Sir, permission to leave the port - you see you weren't allowed to leave t
he port - I asked for permission to leave the port. Four days leave granted. Standing there like a - they give me a pass - I stretched it for ten days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Er - home - well - mother was all right then. I stretched it for ten days w
hen I came back in the barracks there was no word said - me name was up on the draft board there to go an join a ship called the War Curren - I had a gunner then - I'd done that you see. But if she had her .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What exactly did you have to do as a gunloader?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Stand by all the time for - submarines - it was a cargo ship - it was taking cargo and stopped at Norway and .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 You were still on Navy pay were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 Yes - I was in the Navy then. A four inch gun - I only fired it once - submarine
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 How did you get on with the Navy and the battleships?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 
All right. All right. We was - the second voyage we went out - went out to Mobile - Alabama - and we loaded pig iron and cotton and two of the crew, Norwegians, got paid off with all spice
s and the - er - the Captain asked the Chief Officer if - er - I had - a gun crew you see - two others and meself - if any of 'em would - er - act as A.B. A.B.'s pay in the Navy like - ooh and, you tell him I will - this Mate - Chief Officer was - er - ja
w
ing - he says you've been in the merchant's service haven't you? I said blimey I was born in it. And I told him things he never knew - he took me on - all right was two hours - I got on pasls with him fine. He says when the wars over he says you can stay 
on the time in my place and you can - if I'm alive he says you can come in as you like, and he got - I never saw him no more after that voyage. Sent me home to Chatham, be demobilised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 When were you demobilised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid417782 SS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 They didn't demobilize me. No. They sent me up to - to join - er - the Crown Prince Germany's auxillaury lot - a cruiser it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11099359 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3940393\charrsid14709753 What year was this?
