years - he done six bits for it - six bits - that's eighteen years and when he came out he was - er - what you call - er - ensign - like a - full warrant officer - his pension then was five dollars a day a dollar then was twenty shillings and tenpence and
 
he was getting five dollars a day for seven days a week in Liverpool and he was the boss quartermaster of the Ballylarier big German - well he had her - the boss quartermaster - and then he had section money and if he's still alive hise pension must have 
